entry.title: [Site search policy] Save non-validated policy value to pref
entry.content:
This CL creates the basic plumbing needed to save SiteSearchSettings

policy value to a managed pref. The responsibility is shared between

two classes:

- SiteSearchPolicyHandler: the policy logic, responsible for saving to

the pref

- EnterpriseSiteSearchManager: observes changes to the pref, will

eventually update the TemplateURL database



In order to make this CL easier to review, some logic will be added in

follow-up CLs, in particular:

- Policy validation

- Saving the template urls to the database

- Interactions with existing user settings and DSP policies

entry.title: Fuzzing coverage: increase RSS limit.
entry.content:
When run on ClusterFuzz, fuzzers obey extra parameters inside an

.options file which can specify things like a per-fuzzer customized RSS

limit. We don't have that parsing and configuration code available to us

in the LUCI environment, so for now, hard-code a larger RSS limit for

all fuzzers.



This is necessary because we see some fuzzers (e.g.

html_preload_scanner) crashing in the logs by using excessive RSS. It's

not clear whether this is because they naturally use more than the 2GB

default or if it's because specific test cases cause extreme memory

usage (and whether that's a bug). However, such crashes appear to result

in coverage information not being fully written out, thus resulting in

inaccuracies in the fuzzing coverage dashboard.



While we investigate how and whether we can persuade such fuzzers to

write out coverage information even in case of a crash, meanwhile tweak

the RSS limit to perhaps reduce such crashes in the first place.

entry.title: Settings: give "when on/things to consider" headers a heading role
entry.content:
Give "When on/Things to consider" (WO/TTC) headers a programmatic

heading role so that screenreaders correctly read them out as headings.

This CL does this for all WO/TTC descriptions that already use the

centralized settings-columned-section style (crrev.com/c/4902010):

- All privacy guide fragments

- page_content_page

- PS adMeasurement subpage

- speed_page



In a follow-up this should also be done for the security_page and

the old preloading_page.



Note that UIs with WO/TTC descriptions define different heading levels

under which they embed their WO/TTC description. To ensure that the

WO/TTC description is always embedded one level below the embedding

heading level, those UIs individually define which heading level they

want to use with their WO/TTC description headers (h2, h3). See [1]

for details. This CL updates the WO/TTC header style so that WO/TTC

headers look the same for h2 and h3. As a result this CL doesn't cause

any visible UI changes.

entry.title: Fix the confirmation chip's animation
entry.content:
If `gfx::Animation::ShouldRenderRichAnimation()` returns `false` then Chip will have instant animation. That means in `CollapseConfirmation()` started animation will fire a callback immediately, before

`is_waiting_for_confirmation_collapse_` is set to `true`. That impacts

entry.title: Crash GPU process and clear shader cache when skia reports compileError.
entry.content:
Sometimes Skia failed to compile the cached GLSL because the driver had

been changed but GL_RENDERER was still the same. In this case, we better

crash the GPU process and signal the browser to clear the cache & let

Skia regenerate the GLSL in the next run.



Even if the compile failure wasn't caused by the cached GLSL. It's still

better to crash the GPU process and let the shaders be re-generated.

Because a failed compilation would have resulted in wrong rendering

even if we had allowed the process to continue its execution.

entry.title: Paint background invalidation when a table column span changes
entry.content:
Although table column elements (`LayoutTableColumn`) are not laid out,

their background styles will affect the background of the table

columns they span. The set of table columns that a table column

element spans can change, which means the background of the table

might need to change when a `LayoutTableColumn`'s span changes.



However, this is not currently happening because changing the span is

not invalidating the table background. This patch fixes that. As an

optimization, we invalidate the background only if some of the table's

`LayoutTableColumn` have a CSS-specified background.



For this optimization, however, `LayoutTable::HasBackgroundForPaint`

cannot be used, because that will only take into account the

backgrounds of any `LayoutTableColumn`s that span actual columns. It

is possible for a `LayoutTableColumn` that did not span any table

columns to suddenly do so if the span for some previous

`LayoutTableColumn` is decreased. Therefore, we instead added an

anonymous `TableHasColumnsWithBackground` function that checks every

`LayoutTableColumn`.



Bug: 1373252

entry.title: [PA] Implement Lightweight Quarantine
entry.content:
Lightweight Quarantine (LQ) provides a low-cost quarantine mechanism

with following characteristics.

- Built on PartitionAlloc: only supports allocations in a known root

- As fast as PA: LQ just defers `Free()` handling and may benefit from

thread cache etc.

- Thread-safe

- No allocation time information: triggered on `Free()`

- Don't use quarantined objects' payload - available for zapping

- Flexible to support several applications

- TODO(crbug.com/1462223): Implement Miracle Object quarantine with

LQ.

entry.title: [WebNN][CrOS]: Build infrastructure for converting WebNN graph to tflite model
entry.content:
Add a converter class to convert WebNN graph to tflite model and

persist into FlatBuffer. The schema_generated.h file defines the format

for each data structure to serialize, there are below functions:

1, `SerializeBuffer` is to serialize the constant data (e.g. weights)

2, `SerializeTensor` is to serialize tensor for input, constant and

output operand.

3, `SerializeOperation` is to serialize operations, `Relu` is supported

in this CL.
